<!doctype html>
<html lang="en" class="no-js" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/WebPage">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">

  {{> page-title active_process=true }}

  {{> head active_process=true lang_cs=false }}
</head>
<body class="page--process">
  {{> browser-notification }}

  {{> manifest }}

  <main>
    {{> header active_process=true lang_cs=false }}

    <section id="sec__about" class="sec__process">
      <div class="row--process">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="row">
            <div class="col-xs-12 col-md-6 icon-container">
              <img class="svg-icon svg-icon-discovery wp wp-discovery-icon" src="./images/icons/icon-idea.svg" alt="Lightbulb icon">
            </div>

            <div class="col-xs-12 col-md-6 wp wp-discovery-text">
              <h2 class="nutshell__heading">Discovery</h2>

              <p>Exceptional design start by understanding your requirements. I will ask you questions to understand your image, goals, budget, target markets, content requirements, reference sites, materials and desired outcomes. Basically, I will cover everything you know and want at this point so I can create perfect, tailored, design.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="row--process row--black">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="row">
            <div class="col-xs-12 col-md-6 mobile--show icon-container">
              <img class="svg-icon wp wp-planning-icon-mobile" src="./images/icons/icon-map.svg" alt="Map icon">
            </div>

            <div class="col-xs-12 col-md-6 wp wp-planning-text">
              <h2 class="nutshell__heading">Planning</h2>

              <p>Once I have learned what you need, it's time to start planning how we are going to make it happen. I will map out all the parts of the design and create architecture that will work as building foundations in the next phases. I will also create a functional specificationâ€”a document that sets out in detail all the things that must be done and how to get them done.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="col-xs-12 col-md-6 mobile--hide icon-container">
              <img class="svg-icon svg-icon-planning wp wp-planning-icon-desktop" src="./images/icons/icon-map.svg" alt="Map icon">
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="row--process">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="row">
            <div class="col-xs-12 col-md-6 icon-container">
              <img class="svg-icon svg-icon-design wp wp-design-icon" src="./images/icons/icon-pen.svg" alt="Design icon">
            </div>

            <div class="col-xs-12 col-md-6 wp wp-design-text">
              <h2 class="nutshell__heading">Design</h2>

              <p>I will get my creative ideas flowing by sketching and mocking-up different ideas of your design. Choices about design direction, layout, typography, content and color palettes are tested by prototyping a number of ideas. I will identify what works best in order to communicate your goals. Then, I will review the mockups with you and refine until you will be satisfied.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="row--process row--black">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="row">
            <div class="col-xs-12 col-md-6 mobile--show icon-container">
              <img class="svg-icon wp wp-building-icon-mobile" src="./images/icons/icon-rocket.svg" alt="Building icon">
            </div>

            <div class="col-xs-12 col-md-6 wp wp-building-text">
              <h2 class="nutshell__heading">Building</h2>

              <p>Once your killer design is signed off I put your product into development. I will build a working system that will perfectly correspond to the final design idea. Your product is then deployed to a staging environment where I will rigorously test its functionality and fix any bugs. Then, I will hand the system over to you for final testing.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="col-xs-12 col-md-6 mobile--hide icon-container">
              <img class="svg-icon svg-icon-building wp wp-building-icon-desktop" src="./images/icons/icon-rocket.svg" alt="Building icon">
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="row--process">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="row">
            <div class="col-xs-12 col-md-6 icon-container">
              <img class="svg-icon svg-icon-evaluation wp wp-evaluation-icon" src="./images/icons/icon-statistics.svg" alt="Evaluation icon">
            </div>

            <div class="col-xs-12 col-md-6 wp wp-evaluation-text">
              <h2 class="nutshell__heading">Evaluation</h2>

              <p>Evaluation phase is the last part of my design process. I will systematically test the result of my work to see if it achieves your business and project goals. Evaluation will help us find potential weaknesses of my design. Then, I'll use this feedback to fix all of these weaknesses and any other gaps. Result will be flawless and your satisfaction.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          {{> cta-button lang_cs=false }}
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    {{> footer }}
  </main>

  {{> scripts has-waypoints=true }}
</body>
</html>
